PROBLEM SECTION
Title
Identity Has Become Fragmented and Risky
Body
In many organizations, identity is spread across directories, applications, and manual processes.
Authentication is split across systems
Joiner–Mover–Leaver processes are manual
Admin and service accounts are unmanaged
Audit evidence is collected too late
This fragmentation creates operational and regulatory risk.
SOLUTION SECTION
Title
dmfIAM: One Identity Provider. Full Control.
Body
dmfIAM acts as the central Identity Provider for your organization.
It manages:
Who identities are
How they authenticate
What they are allowed to access
How access changes over time
All from a single, auditable platform.
WHAT dmfIAM DELIVERS
Identity Lifecycle Management
Joiner–Mover–Leaver automation
Identity status and lifecycle enforcement
Central Authorization
Role-based access control (RBAC)
Policy-driven authorization
Privileged Identity Control
Admin and service account lifecycle
Clear ownership and accountability
Authentication & Federation
Native authentication
SSO and federation to AD and Microsoft Entra
Integration & Extensibility
APIs for external systems
Integration with physical access and infrastructure
Governance & Auditability
Audit logs
Access reviews
Approval workflows
Self-service portals
