PRODUCT & COMPLIANCE — CORRECTED NARRATIVE
PRODUCT PAGE — KEY SHIFT
Title
Central Identity Provider with Built-In Governance
Core message
dmfIAM is not an add-on or overlay.
It is the identity authority that applications, directories, and services rely on.
Architecture (described, not diagram-heavy)
dmfIAM stores and governs identities
Applications authenticate against dmfIAM
AD and Entra integrate via federation or synchronization
Authorization decisions are made centrally
COMPLIANCE PAGE — KEY SHIFT
Title
Identity as a Regulated Control
Core message
When identity is the system of record, governance becomes enforceable — not advisory.
What this enables
Enforced Joiner–Mover–Leaver
Central approval policies
Immutable audit trails
Clear separation of duties
Critical Infrastructure & IKT
dmfIAM supports IKT expectations by:
Acting as a single identity authority
Governing privileged and service accounts
Providing traceable authentication and authorization
Integrating with infrastructure and physical access systems
